Section 1. That section 123.14 of the Revised Code be 5
enacted to read as follows: 6
Sec. 123.14. (A) Every two years, the department of 7
administrative services shall conduct a comprehensive study and 8
issue a report on all real property owned or leased by the state 9
or a state agency. The director of administrative services shall 10
deliver the report to the speaker of the house of 11
representatives, the president of the senate, and the governor 12
not later than the thirty-first day of January of every odd- 13
numbered year. The study shall include all of the following: 14
(1) A complete list of all the real property owned by the 15
state or a state agency. The list shall be organized by who owns 16
the real property, which shall include information regarding the 17
nature of the real property, such as whether the real property 18
includes structures, whether any structure is office space, the 19

